nncFrIntStatistics.name: nncFrIntStatistics
nncFrIntStatistics.contactinfo: Newbridge Networks Corporation Postal: 600 March Road Kanata, Ontario Canada K2K 2E6 Phone: +1 613 591 3600 Fax: +1 613 591 3680
nncFrIntStatistics.description: This module contains definitions for performance monitoring of Frame Relay Streams

nncFrStrStatCurrentTable.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentTable
nncFrStrStatCurrentTable.description: The nncFrStrStatCurrentTable contains objects for monitoring the performance of a frame relay stream during the current 1hr interval.

nncFrStrStatCurrentEntry.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentEntry
nncFrStrStatCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the 1hr current statistics table. Each conceptual row contains current interval statistics for a particular frame relay stream.

nncFrStrStatCurrentState.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentState
nncFrStrStatCurrentState.description: The state of the current interval. The object provides a status for those entries which have been reset by the user or have been subject to a wall-clock time change.

nncFrStrStatCurrentAbsoluteIntervalNumbe.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentAbsoluteIntervalNumber
nncFrStrStatCurrentAbsoluteIntervalNumbe.description: The absolute interval number of this interval.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInOctets.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInOctets
nncFrStrStatCurrentInOctets.description: Number of bytes received on this stream.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutOctets.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutOctets
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutOctets.description: Number of bytes transmitted on this stream.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInUCastPackets.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatCurrentInUCastPackets.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames received.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutUCastPackets.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutUCastPackets.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames transmitted.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscards.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscards
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscards.description: Number of incoming frames discarded due to these reasons: policing, congestion.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscards.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscards
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscards.description: Number of outgoing frames discarded due to these reasons: policing, congestion.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInErrors.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInErrors
nncFrStrStatCurrentInErrors.description: Number of incoming frames discarded due to errors: invalid lengths, non-integral bytes, CRC errors, bad encapsulation, invalid EA, reserved DLCI

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutErrors.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutErrors
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutErrors.description: Number of outgoing frames discarded due to errors: eg. bad encapsulation.

nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserProtErrors.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserProtErrors
nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserProtErrors.description: Number of user-side local in-channel signalling protocol errors (protocol discriminator, message type, call reference & mandatory information eleement errors) for this uni/nni stream. If the stream is not perfor- ming user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetProtErrors.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetProtErrors
nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetProtErrors.description: Number of network-side local in-channel signalling protocol errors (protocol discriminator, message type, call reference & mandatory information eleement errors) for this uni/nni stream. If the stream is not perfor- ming network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserLinkRelErrors.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserLinkRelErrors
nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserLinkRelErrors.description: Number of user-side local in-channel signalling link reliability errors (non receipt of Enq/Status messages or invalid sequence numbers in a link integrity verifi- cation information element) for this stream. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetLinkRelErrors.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetLinkRelErrors
nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetLinkRelErrors.description: Number of network-side local in-channel signalling link reliability errors (non receipt of Enq/Status messages or invalid sequence numbers in a link integrity verification information element) for this stream. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserChanInactive.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserChanInactive
nncFrStrStatCurrentSigUserChanInactive.description: Number of times the user-side channel was declared inactive (N2 errors in N3 events) for this stream. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetChanInactive.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetChanInactive
nncFrStrStatCurrentSigNetChanInactive.description: Number of times the network-side channel was declared inactive (N2 errors in N3 events) for this stream. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStSCAlarms.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStSCAlarms
nncFrStrStatCurrentStSCAlarms.description: Number of one second intervals for which the stream entered the severely congested state.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStTimeSC.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStTimeSC
nncFrStrStatCurrentStTimeSC.description: Period of time the stream was in the severely congested state during the current interval (expressed in 10's of milliseconds). Divide into the entire length of the interval to get a ratio.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStMaxDurationRED.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStMaxDurationRED
nncFrStrStatCurrentStMaxDurationRED.description: Longest period of time the stream spent in the Red (severely congested) state, expressed in seconds.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStMCAlarms.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStMCAlarms
nncFrStrStatCurrentStMCAlarms.description: Number of one second intervals for which the stream entered the mildly congested state.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStTimeMC.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStTimeMC
nncFrStrStatCurrentStTimeMC.description: Period of time the stream was in the mildly congested state during the current interval (expressed in 10's of milliseconds). Divide into the entire length of the interval to get a ratio.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutLinkUtilization.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutLinkUtilization
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutLinkUtilization.description: The percentage utilization on the outgoing link during the current interval.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInLinkUtilization.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInLinkUtilization
nncFrStrStatCurrentInLinkUtilization.description: The percentage utilization on the incoming link during the current interval.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInInvdLength.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInInvdLength
nncFrStrStatCurrentInInvdLength.description: Number of frames discarded because there was no data in the frame, or because the frame exceeded the maximum allowed length.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLastErroredDLCI.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLastErroredDLCI
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLastErroredDLCI.description: DLCI of the most recent DLC to receive invalid frames on this frame stream.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdOctetsCOS.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdOctetsCOS
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdOctetsCOS.description: Number of ingress bytes discarded due to receive Class-of-Service procedures.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdCOSDESet.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdCOSDESet
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdCOSDESet.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to receive Class-of-Service procedures, in which the DE bit was set.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdCOSDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdCOSDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdCOSDEClr.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to receive Class-of-Service procedures, in which the DE bit was not set.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdBadEncaps.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdBadEncaps
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdBadEncaps.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to having a bad RFC1490 encapsulation header.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdBadEncaps.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdBadEncaps
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdBadEncaps.description: Number of egress frames discarded due to having a bad RFC1483 encapsulation header.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdUnsupEncaps.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdUnsupEncaps
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdUnsupEncaps.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to having an unsupported RFC1490 encapsulation header.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdUnsupEncaps.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdUnsupEncaps
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdUnsupEncaps.description: Number of egress frames discarded due to having an unsupported RFC1483 encapsulation header.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdDESet.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdDESet
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdDESet.description: Number of egress frames discarded due to transmit congestion procedures, in which the DE bit was set.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutDiscdDEClr.description: Number of egress frames discarded due to transmit congestion procedures, in which the DE bit was not set.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdDESet.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdDESet
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdDESet.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to receive congestion procedures, in which the DE bit was set.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentInDiscdDEClr.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to receive congestion procedures, in which the DE bit was not set.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldField.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldField
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldField.description: Number of Status signalling frames with incorrect values for the Unnumbered Information Frame field, Protocol Discrimator field, or Call Reference Field.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigUnsupMsgType.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigUnsupMsgType
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigUnsupMsgType.description: Number of Status signalling frames that are not a Status or Status Enquiry messsage (Unsupported message type).

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldEID.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldEID
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldEID.description: Number of Status signalling frames with an IEID that is not a Report Type IEID, Keep Alive Sequence IEID, or a PVC Status IEID.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldIELen.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldIELen
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldIELen.description: Number of Status signalling frames with an IE length field size that does not conform with the Frame Relay status signalling protocol.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldRepType.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldRepType
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigInvldRepType.description: Number of Status signalling frames with a Report Type IE that were not a Full Report Type or a Keep Alive Confirmation.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigFrmWithNoIEs.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigFrmWithNoIEs
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMSigFrmWithNoIEs.description: Number of Status signalling frames that terminate before the IE appears.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStUserSequenceErrs.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStUserSequenceErrs
nncFrStrStatCurrentStUserSequenceErrs.description: Number of status signalling frames received with a Last Received Sequence number that is inconsistent with the expected value, the last transmitted Current Sequence Number. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStNetSequenceErrs.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStNetSequenceErrs
nncFrStrStatCurrentStNetSequenceErrs.description: Number of status signalling frames received with a Last Received Sequence number that is inconsistent with the expected value, the last transmitted Current Sequence Number. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUTimeoutsnT1.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUTimeoutsnT1
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUTimeoutsnT1.description: Number of times the link integrity verification interval has been exceeded without receiving a Status message. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUStatusMsgsRcvd.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUStatusMsgsRcvd
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUStatusMsgsRcvd.description: Number of Status messages received. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUStatusENQMsgsSen.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUStatusENQMsgsSent
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUStatusENQMsgsSen.description: Number of Status Enquiry messages sent. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUAsyncStatusRcvd.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUAsyncStatusRcvd
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMUAsyncStatusRcvd.description: Number of asynchronous Update Status messages received. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNTimeoutsnT2.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNTimeoutsnT2
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNTimeoutsnT2.description: Number of times the polling verification interval was exceeded without receivung a Keep Alive Sequence. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNStatusMsgsSent.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNStatusMsgsSent
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNStatusMsgsSent.description: Number of Status messages sent. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNStatusENQMsgsRcv.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNStatusENQMsgsRcvd
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNStatusENQMsgsRcv.description: Number of Status Enquiry messages received. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNAsyncStatusSent.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNAsyncStatusSent
nncFrStrStatCurrentStLMNAsyncStatusSent.description: Number of asynchronous Update Status messages transmitted. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInCRCErrors.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInCRCErrors
nncFrStrStatCurrentInCRCErrors.description: Number of frames with an incorrect CRC-16 value.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInNonIntegral.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInNonIntegral
nncFrStrStatCurrentInNonIntegral.description: Number of frames with a non-integral number of octets between the delimiting HDLC flags.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInReservedDLCI.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInReservedDLCI
nncFrStrStatCurrentInReservedDLCI.description: Number of frames with a DLCI that cannot be assigned to user connections.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInInvldEA.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInInvldEA
nncFrStrStatCurrentInInvldEA.description: Number of frames with the EA (extended address) bit incorrectly set.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStFrmTooSmall.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStFrmTooSmall
nncFrStrStatCurrentStFrmTooSmall.description: Number of frames that are smaller than the allowed minimum size.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInSumOfDisagremnts.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInSumOfDisagremnts
nncFrStrStatCurrentInSumOfDisagremnts.description: Total number of frames discarded because: the frame relay UNI or ICI was unavailable to accept frame traffic, the frame had a DLCI not available for end-user connections, the DLCI was inactive, the frame exceeded the maximum configured frame length (but its length was legal within the frame relay protocol), the frame violated the configured address field size (but had a legal address field size with the frame relay protocol), or was an unexpected status signalling frame.

nncFrStrStatCurrentInOverRuns.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentInOverRuns
nncFrStrStatCurrentInOverRuns.description: Number of times the receiver was forced to overrun.

nncFrStrStatCurrentOutUnderRuns.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentOutUnderRuns
nncFrStrStatCurrentOutUnderRuns.description: Number of times the transmitter was forced to underrun.

nncFrStrStatCurrentStIntervalDuration.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentStIntervalDuration
nncFrStrStatCurrentStIntervalDuration.description: Duration of the statistics accumulation interval.

nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortPeakDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortPeakDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortPeakDelay.description: The largest delay experienced by any frame that was transmitted on the stream in service category Best Effort.

nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedPeakDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedPeakDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedPeakDelay.description: The largest delay experienced by any frame that was transmitted on the stream in service category: Committed Throughptut.

nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayPeakDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayPeakDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayPeakDelay.description: The largest delay experienced by any frame that was transmitted on the stream in service category: Low Delay.

nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimePeakDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimePeakDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimePeakDelay.description: The largest delay experienced by any frame that was transmitted on the stream in service category Real Time.

nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortAccDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortAccDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortAccDelay.description: The accumulated delay experienced by all frames in a stream transmitted in service category Best Effort. Combined with the Out Ucast Packets for service category Best Effort, the average delay per frame can be calculated.

nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedAccDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedAccDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedAccDelay.description: The accumulated delay experienced by all frames in a stream transmitted in service category Committed Throughput. Combined with the Out Ucast Packets for service category Committed Throughput, the average delay per frame can be calculated.

nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayAccDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayAccDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayAccDelay.description: The accumulated delay experienced by all frames in a stream transmitted in service category Low Delay. Combined with the Out Ucast Packets for service category Low Delay, the average delay per frame can be calculated.

nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeAccDelay.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeAccDelay
nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeAccDelay.description: The accumulated delay experienced by all frames in a stream transmitted in service category Real Time. Combined with the Out Ucast Packets for service category Real Time, the average delay per frame can be calculated.

nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortOutUCastPac.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortOutUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortOutUCastPac.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames transmitted in service category Best Effort.

nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedOutUCastPack.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedOutUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedOutUCastPack.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames transmitted in service category Committed Throughput.

nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayOutUCastPacke.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayOutUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayOutUCastPacke.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames transmitted in service category Low Delay.

nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeOutUCastPacke.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeOutUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeOutUCastPacke.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames transmitted in service category Real Time.

nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortUCastPacket.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortUCastPacketsDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortUCastPacket.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set transmitted in service category Best Effort.

nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedUCastPackets.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedUCastPacketsDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedUCastPackets.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set transmitted in service category Committed Throughput.

nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayUCastPacketsD.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayUCastPacketsDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayUCastPacketsD.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set transmitted in service category Low Delay.

nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeUCastPacketsD.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeUCastPacketsDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeUCastPacketsD.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set, transmitted in service category Real Time.

nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortDiscdDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortDiscdDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentBestEffortDiscdDEClr.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set, discarded by QoS procedures in service category Best Effort.

nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedDiscdDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedDiscdDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentCommittedDiscdDEClr.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set, discarded by QoS procedures in service category Committed Throughput.

nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayDiscdDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayDiscdDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentLowDelayDiscdDEClr.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set, discarded by QoS procedures in service category Low Delay.

nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeDiscdDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeDiscdDEClr
nncFrStrStatCurrentRealTimeDiscdDEClr.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames with the DE bit not set, discarded by QoS procedures in service category Real Time.

nncFrStrStatIntervalTable.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalTable
nncFrStrStatIntervalTable.description: The nncFrStrStatIntervalTable contains objects for monitoring the performance of a frame relay stream over M historical intervals of 1hr each.

nncFrStrStatIntervalEntry.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalEntry
nncFrStrStatIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the 1hr interval statistics table. Each conceptual row contains interval statistics for a par- ticular interval on a particular stream.

nncFrStrStatIntervalNumber.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalNumber
nncFrStrStatIntervalNumber.description: The interval number (N) of the statistics in this row.

nncFrStrStatIntervalState.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalState
nncFrStrStatIntervalState.description: The state of the interval represented by this row. The object provides a status for those entries which have been reset by the user or subject to a wall-clock time change.

nncFrStrStatIntervalAbsoluteIntervalNumb.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalAbsoluteIntervalNumber
nncFrStrStatIntervalAbsoluteIntervalNumb.description: The absolute interval number of this interval.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInOctets.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInOctets
nncFrStrStatIntervalInOctets.description: Number of bytes received on this stream.

nncFrStrStatIntervalOutOctets.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalOutOctets
nncFrStrStatIntervalOutOctets.description: Number of bytes transmitted on this stream.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInUCastPackets.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatIntervalInUCastPackets.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames received.

nncFrStrStatIntervalOutUCastPackets.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalOutUCastPackets
nncFrStrStatIntervalOutUCastPackets.description: Number of unerrored, unicast frames transmitted.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscards.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscards
nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscards.description: Number of incoming frames discarded due to these reasons: policing, congestion.

nncFrStrStatIntervalOutDiscards.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalOutDiscards
nncFrStrStatIntervalOutDiscards.description: Number of outgoing frames discarded due to these reasons: policing, congestion.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInErrors.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInErrors
nncFrStrStatIntervalInErrors.description: Number of incoming frames discarded due to errors: eg. invalid lengths, non-integral bytes...

nncFrStrStatIntervalOutErrors.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalOutErrors
nncFrStrStatIntervalOutErrors.description: Number of outgoing frames discarded due to errors: eg. bad encapsulation.

nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserProtErrors.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserProtErrors
nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserProtErrors.description: Number of user-side local in-channel signalling protocol errors (protocol discriminator, message type, call reference & mandatory information eleement errors) for this uni/nni stream. If the stream is not perfor- ming user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetProtErrors.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetProtErrors
nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetProtErrors.description: Number of network-side local in-channel signalling protocol errors (protocol discriminator, message type, call reference & mandatory information eleement errors) for this uni/nni stream. If the stream is not perfor- ming network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserLinkRelErrors.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserLinkRelErrors
nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserLinkRelErrors.description: Number of user-side local in-channel signalling link reliability errors (non receipt of Enq/Status messages or invalid sequence numbers in a link integrity verifi- cation information element) for this stream. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetLinkRelErrors.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetLinkRelErrors
nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetLinkRelErrors.description: Number of network-side local in-channel signalling link reliability errors (non receipt of Enq/Status messages or invalid sequence numbers in a link integrity verification information element) for this stream. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserChanInactive.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserChanInactive
nncFrStrStatIntervalSigUserChanInactive.description: Number of times the user-side channel was declared inactive (N2 errors in N3 events) for this stream. If the stream is not performing user-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetChanInactive.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetChanInactive
nncFrStrStatIntervalSigNetChanInactive.description: Number of times the network-side channel was declared inactive (N2 errors in N3 events) for this stream. If the stream is not performing network-side procedures, this value is equal to noSuchName.

nncFrStrStatIntervalStSCAlarms.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalStSCAlarms

nncFrStrStatIntervalStTimeSC.description: Period of time the stream was in the severely congested state during the designated interval (expressed in 10's of milliseconds). Divide into the entire length of the interval to get a ratio.

nncFrStrStatIntervalStMaxDurationRED.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalStMaxDurationRED
nncFrStrStatIntervalStMaxDurationRED.description: Longest period of time the stream spent in the Red (severely congested) state, expressed in seconds.

nncFrStrStatIntervalStMCAlarms.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalStMCAlarms
nncFrStrStatIntervalStMCAlarms.description: Number of one second intervals for which the stream entered the mildly congested state.

nncFrStrStatIntervalStTimeMC.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalStTimeMC
nncFrStrStatIntervalStTimeMC.description: Period of time the stream was in the mildly congested state during the designated interval (expressed in 10's of milliseconds). Divide into the entire length of the interval to get a ratio.

nncFrStrStatIntervalOutLinkUtilization.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalOutLinkUtilization
nncFrStrStatIntervalOutLinkUtilization.description: The percentage utilization on the outgoing link during the designated interval.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInLinkUtilization.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInLinkUtilization
nncFrStrStatIntervalInLinkUtilization.description: The percentage utilization on the incoming link during the designated interval.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInInvdLength.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInInvdLength
nncFrStrStatIntervalInInvdLength.description: Number of frames discarded because there was no data in the frame, or because the frame exceeded the maximum allowed length.

nncFrStrStatIntervalStLastErroredDLCI.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalStLastErroredDLCI
nncFrStrStatIntervalStLastErroredDLCI.description: DLCI of the most recent DLC to receive invalid frames on this frame stream.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdOctetsCOS.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdOctetsCOS
nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdOctetsCOS.description: Number of ingress bytes discarded due to receive Class-of-Service procedures.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDESet.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDESet
nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDESet.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to receive Class-of-Service procedures, in which the DE bit was set.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDEClr.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDEClr
nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDEClr.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to receive Class-of-Service procedures, in which the DE bit was not set.

nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdBadEncaps.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdBadEncaps
nncFrStrStatIntervalInDiscdBadEncaps.description: Number of ingress frames discarded due to having a bad RFC1490 encapsulation header.

nncFrStrStatIntervalOutDiscdBadEncaps.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalOutDiscdBadEncaps

nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDEClr.name: nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDEClr
nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalInDiscdCOSDEClr.description: Number of frames discarded for the PVC Endpoint due to receive class of service procedures, in which the DE bit was not set.

nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdDESet.name: nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdDESet
nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdDESet.description: Number of frames discarded for the PVC Endpoint due to transmit congestion procedures, in which the DE bit was set.

nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdDEClr.name: nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdDEClr
nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdDEClr.description: Number of frames discarded for the PVC Endpoint due to transmit congestion procedures, in which the DE bit was not set.

nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdBadEnca.name: nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdBadEncaps
nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdBadEnca.description: Number of frames discarded for the PVC Endpoint due to having a bad RFC1483 encapsulation header.

nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdUnsupEn.name: nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdUnsupEncaps
nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalOutDiscdUnsupEn.description: Number of frames discarded for the PVC Endpoint due to having an unsupported RFC1483 encapsulation header.

nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalStReasDiscards.name: nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalStReasDiscards
nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalStReasDiscards.description: Number of frames discarded for the PVC Endpoint due to any reassembly errors.

nncFrDepthOfHistoricalStrata.name: nncFrDepthOfHistoricalStrata
nncFrDepthOfHistoricalStrata.description: Depth of historical strata of FR interval statistics.

nncFrStrBertStatTable.name: nncFrStrBertStatTable
nncFrStrBertStatTable.description: The nncFrStrBertStatTable contains objects for reporting the current statistics of a BERT being performed on a frame relay stream. This feature is introduced in Rel 2.2 frame relay cards.

nncFrStrBertStatEntry.name: nncFrStrBertStatEntry
nncFrStrBertStatEntry.description: An entry in the BERT statistics table. Each conceptual row contains statistics related to the BERT being performed on a specific DLCI within a particular frame relay stream.

nncFrStrBertDlci.name: nncFrStrBertDlci
nncFrStrBertDlci.description: This object indicates if there is a BERT active on the frame relay stream, and when active on which DLCI the BERT is active on. WHERE: 0 = BERT not active, non-zero = DLCI

nncFrStrBertStatStatus.name: nncFrStrBertStatStatus
nncFrStrBertStatStatus.description: The current status of the BERT when the BERT is activated: where 0 = Loss of pattern sync. 1 = Pattern Sync.

nncFrStrBertStatTxFrames.name: nncFrStrBertStatTxFrames
nncFrStrBertStatTxFrames.description: The number of Frames transmitted onto the stream by BERT Task. Each BERT Frame is of a fixed size and contains a fixed pattern.

nncFrStrBertStatRxFrames.name: nncFrStrBertStatRxFrames
nncFrStrBertStatRxFrames.description: The number of Frames received while the BERT is in pattern sync. The Rx Frame count will only be incremented when in pattern sync and the received packet is the correct size and contains the DLCI being BERTED.

nncFrStrBertStatRxBytes.name: nncFrStrBertStatRxBytes
nncFrStrBertStatRxBytes.description: The number of Bytes transmitted onto the stream by BERT Task. Each BERT packet is of a fixed size and contains a fixed pattern.

nncFrStrBertStatTxBytes.name: nncFrStrBertStatTxBytes
nncFrStrBertStatTxBytes.description: The number of Bytes transmitted while the BERT is in pattern sync. The Tx Byte count will only be incremented when in pattern sync.

nncFrStrBertStatRxErrors.name: nncFrStrBertStatRxErrors
nncFrStrBertStatRxErrors.description: The number of errors detected in the received packets while the BERT is in pattern sync. Packets flagged as having CRC errors that contain the DLCI being BERTED and the correct packet size being BERTED will be scanned for errors and the number of errors accumulated in this counter.

nncFrStrBertStatEstErrors.name: nncFrStrBertStatEstErrors
nncFrStrBertStatEstErrors.description: The estimated number of errors encountered by the packets being transmitted while the BERT is in pattern sync based on the fact that the packets are not returned, and pattern sync is maintained.

nncFrStrStatCurrentGroup.name: nncFrStrStatCurrentGroup
nncFrStrStatCurrentGroup.description: Collection of objects providing 1hr current statistics for a FR stream.

nncFrStrStatIntervalGroup.name: nncFrStrStatIntervalGroup
nncFrStrStatIntervalGroup.description: Collection of objects providing 1hr interval statistics for a FR stream.

nncFrPVCEndptStatCurrentGroup.name: nncFrPVCEndptStatCurrentGroup
nncFrPVCEndptStatCurrentGroup.description: Collection of objects providing 1hr current statistics for a FR PVC Endpoint.

nncFrPVCEndptStatIntervalGroup.description: Collection of objects providing 1hr current statistics for a FR PVC Endpoint.
